<dl id="n19070e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n19" href="#n19070e">N19 (VI.B.19)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n19all.htm#n19070e"> 70(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> direct tradition</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The illness, the occurrence of which is also corroborated by <mark>direct tradition</mark>, makes it reasonable to refer the event to the summer, and, since the child was born on Christmas Day, to assume his age was <i>n</i> + 1&frac12; years. <small> Sigmund Freud, <a name="SFWM2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SFWM2"><cite title="source">&ldquo;From the History of an Infantile Neurosis (The &lsquo;Wolf Man&rsquo;)&rdquo;</cite></a> (1925) 508</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
